+    // Local-dev fallback: a network-declaring extension capability with no
+    // per-credential audience (e.g. a custom WASM tool that calls a public API
+    // such as OSV.dev) still needs a non-empty allowlist. Without one, the
+    // host's network obligation validation rejects the empty-but-constrained
+    // policy and the tool cannot execute at all. Grant a broad allowlist scoped
+    // to local-dev; private/metadata/loopback IP ranges stay blocked via
+    // deny_private_ip_ranges. Extensions that carry credential audiences
+    // (gmail, exa web search, ...) already populated `targets` above and are
+    // unaffected by this branch.
+    if targets.is_empty() && capability.effects.contains(&EffectKind::Network) {
+        targets.push(NetworkTargetPattern {
+            scheme: None,
+            host_pattern: "*".to_string(),
+            port: None,
+        });
+    }
     NetworkPolicy {
         allowed_targets: targets,
         deny_private_ip_ranges: true,
